  <data key="d3">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d4">"A beneficiary is a person designated to receive the benefit if the insured person dies, and can be named by the policyholder."&lt;SEP&gt;"A beneficiary is a person designated to receive the insurance benefit upon the death of the insured. This can include spouse, child, friend, or any other individual."&lt;SEP&gt;"An individual designated to receive insurance proceeds upon the policyholder’s death."&lt;SEP&gt;"The beneficiary is a person who may receive benefits from the insurance policy, if applicable."&lt;SEP&gt;"The individual designated to receive the policy benefits upon the insured's death."&lt;SEP&gt;"The individual who receives insurance proceeds directly, without going through the estate."&lt;SEP&gt;"The individual(s) designated in writing to receive the policy benefits."&lt;SEP&gt;"The person or persons named in writing to receive the benefits of the policy."</data>
