  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"PROCESS"</data>
  <data key="d4">"Reinstatement is the process of restoring a lapsed policy to active status, as detailed in the 'Putting your policy back into effect' section."&lt;SEP&gt;"The process of restoring a lapsed policy, provided the insured person is alive."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-cb04334968af2cf23772b1234fa1ff3c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9e48b2c7f5c340d231cab1e863dc3229</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SURRENDER THE POLICY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"ACTION"</data>
  <data key="d4">"The act of terminating the insurance policy, which requires consent from an irrevocable beneficiary."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-b8865028ed52b3b23f75c2db4581d310</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;OCTOBER 7, 2023&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"DATE"</data>
  <data key="d4">"October 7, 2023 is the date when the first premium payment is due."&lt;SEP&gt;"October 7, 2023 is the first premium due date, repeated in the policy schedule."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-15042c9c78a8efe744537c5c84db0f52</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;RELATED CAUSE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"CAUSE"</data>
  <data key="d4">"A recurrence from a related cause is treated as a continuation of the original period."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-6e3c19fad0ec74d4024195693875376d</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PHONE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"COMMUNICATION METHOD"</data>
  <data key="d4">"TD may contact you by phone."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d74a69ffda2d0b7001588e51837113ef</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CALENDAR MONTH&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"TIME PERIOD"</data>
  <data key="d4">"Subsequent monthly premiums are due one calendar month after the previous due date."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-cb04334968af2cf23772b1234fa1ff3c</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;TD LIFE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d4">"A financial institution responsible for processing beneficiary changes and issuing confirmation letters."&lt;SEP&gt;"TD Life is a financial institution that processes beneficiary changes but does not guarantee their legal validity."&lt;SEP&gt;"TD Life is an organization offering insurance products, and purchasing insurance is not required to obtain other products or services."&lt;SEP&gt;"TD Life is an organization that may require supplementary applications or forms to be submitted as part of the application process."&lt;SEP&gt;"TD Life is an organization whose terms include those acting on its behalf."&lt;SEP&gt;"TD Life is authorized to receive information from heirs and estate administrators for claims."&lt;SEP&gt;"TD Life is relieved of responsibility after paying a trust."&lt;SEP&gt;"TD Life is the organization that can be informed to stop direct marketing contact."&lt;SEP&gt;"TD Life may report personal health information to MIB."&lt;SEP&gt;"TD Life records the beneficiary change."&lt;SEP&gt;"The company to which the application and forms are submitted."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d6297aea6185daf9585122e54b144c60&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b8865028ed52b3b23f75c2db4581d310&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-dfd5028f0b43132db8da74961939d00d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e336bc3335eae1b8a9a02061f363f289</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;HEALTH QUESTION CONFIRMATION RESPONSES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"DOCUMENT"</data>
  <data key="d4">"These are documents that confirm the responses provided to health-related questions during the application process. They must be reviewed for accuracy."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-7c9b2d4d50f1eb65ffb1c24f16aaff10</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;LAPSED POLICY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"DOCUMENT STATUS"</data>
  <data key="d4">"A lapsed policy is one that has terminated due to non-payment of premiums."&lt;SEP&gt;"A policy that has ended due to non-payment."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-cb04334968af2cf23772b1234fa1ff3c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9e48b2c7f5c340d231cab1e863dc3229</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;QUEBEC&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"LOCATION"</data>
  <data key="d4">"A province in Canada where spouses are automatically irrevocable beneficiaries unless otherwise specified."&lt;SEP&gt;"Legal actions in Quebec are governed by the Civil Code of Quebec."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-b8865028ed52b3b23f75c2db4581d310&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d797d61d4936328367b970f1b1a2a94b</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;MONTHLY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"PAYMENT FREQUENCY"</data>
  <data key="d4">"Monthly is the frequency at which premium payments are required."&lt;SEP&gt;"Monthly is the payment frequency, repeated in the policy schedule."&lt;SEP&gt;"The default payment frequency after waiver."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-15042c9c78a8efe744537c5c84db0f52&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d797d61d4936328367b970f1b1a2a94b</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CONTINUATION OF FORMER PERIOD&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"STATUS"</data>
  <data key="d4">"The second period of total disability is considered a continuation of the first if it occurs within 6 months."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-6e3c19fad0ec74d4024195693875376d</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;TEXT&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
